enhanced_by.reason: The wrap method is the inverse operation of unwrap, making it useful for setting up scenarios where elements are wrapped before being unwrapped.
Both methods modify the DOM structure by either removing elements or their wrappers, making them useful for setting up different DOM states.
After unwrapping elements, it might be necessary to remove the elements themselves to clean up the DOM, making remove a useful method to invoke after unwrap.
Traversing the DOM after unwrapping can help verify the state of the DOM and ensure that the unwrap operation has been correctly applied.
